  "prompt": "What are some karaoke songs for a 2nd alto?",
  "response": "Finding the right karaoke songs for a second alto involves selecting pieces that comfortably fit within your vocal range. Second altos generally sing in a lower register, though they can occasionally reach into the mezzo-soprano range. Here are some karaoke suggestions across different genres:\n\n### Pop/Rock\n1. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele** - This has a strong alto range with emotional depth.\n2. **\"Stay\" by Rihanna ft. Mikky Ekko** - Smooth and comfortably within a lower register.\n3. **\"Fast Car\" by Tracy Chapman** - A storytelling song with a melodic alto line.\n4. **\"Back to Black\" by Amy Winehouse** - Rich, soulful, and well-suited to second altos.\n5. **\"Royals\" by Lorde** - A contemporary, low-range hit.\n\n### Classic Hits\n1. **\"Son of a Preacher Man\" by Dusty Springfield** - A soul classic with a comfortable alto range.\n2. **\"Jolene\" by Dolly Parton** - Although originally by a soprano, it can be beautifully interpreted by an alto with its repetitive and catchy lines.\n3. **\"Dreams\" by Fleetwood Mac** - Stevie Nicks' alto range makes this a perfect fit.\n4. **\"Natural Woman\" by Aretha Franklin** - Filled with emotion and depth.\n\n### Jazz/Soul\n1. **\"At Last\" by Etta James** - A timeless classic that allows an alto to shine.\n2. **\"Feeling Good\" by Nina Simone** - Powerful and dramatic, sitting well in an alto range.\n3. **\"Cry Me a River\" by Julie London** - A moody jazz standard for lower voices.\n\n### Musical Theatre\n1. **\"I Dreamed a Dream\" from Les Mis\u00e9rables** - A musical theatre classic with a range that's great for altos.\n2. **\"Don't Cry for Me Argentina\" from Evita** - Evocative and dramatic with an expansive range.\n3. **\"Memory\" from Cats** - Typically sung by altos or low mezzos.\n\n### Country/Folk\n1. **\"Breathe\" by Faith Hill** - A mellow country hit that fits in an alto range.\n2. **\"Jolene\" by Dolly Parton** - With its storytelling aspect, it suits the warm tone of a second alto.\n3. **\"Before He Cheats\" by Carrie Underwood** - Offers powerhouse moments and suits a lower range.\n\nWhen choosing karaoke songs, try to pick ones that you love and feel comfortable singing, as this will make your performance more enjoyable and convincing.",
